        <li class="alt" id="comment-356819">
            39.&nbsp;&nbsp;            <cite>Ben O.</cite> Says:
                        <br />

            <small class="commentmetadata"><a href="#comment-356819" title="">February 6th, 2011 at 2:26 pm</a> </small>
<div>            <p>Hi Phil- This is a great resource.  I flew back from Tucson to the Netherlands via Atlanta on Feb. 1st (getting in the 2nd).  We had quite some tailwinds on both flights, especially from ATL-AMS, and it&#8217;s not hard to see why.  But, now in Leiden, we have been having some incredibly windy days these past 3 days (Feb. 4-6) from the southwest, and I&#8217;m trying to find out if this is the same weather system.  Actually, what would be helpful is a worldwide satellite movie over several days, but I haven&#8217;t found anything yet.  Do you know of any sites?</p>
            </div> 

        </li>

    
            
